  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Pacianus, After AD 343, bishop of Barcinona (modern Barcelona),
    died before 393; of his life practically nothing is known. Three letters from him to the Novatian Sympronianus survive,
    in which he opposes Novatianism (Novatianus) (CPL 561), also a pamphlet Paraenesis sive Exhortatorius Libellus ad Paenitentiam 
    (Exhortation to Penitence, CPL 562) and a Sermo de Baptismo (Sermon on Baptism, CPL 563)...."
    Markschies, Christoph (Berlin), “Pacianus”, in: Brill’s New Pauly, Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Consulted online on 08 November 2016
  </mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Ecrits, 1995: t.p. (Pacien de Barcelone) p. 13 (Paciano de Barcelona, Pacià de Barcelona) p. 25 
    (Bishop of Barcelona, d. between 379 and 393; it is impossible to be more precise)</mads:note>
